reviewText: I have purchased all 8 Seasons of Touched By An Angel and I will be buying from Amazon.com (No Merchants!!) Season 9, thefinal Season on November 19, 2013. Most of the episodes are ok, and some of them are not so good. As a non-denominationalchristian, it saddens me that none of or very few of the episodes dwell on the disbelief of Lord Jesus Christ/or GOD period!!The ignorance of not knowing your creator is truly sad and unbelievable!!!! Let alone not even having a relationship with ourCreator. Most of all of these episodes dwell on "Angels" but do not dwell on where these celestial beings come from!!! they werecreated just as human beings; the universe; and this world we live in was created. I wish that the writers and executive producersspent more time concentrating on who GOD, OUR FATHER IS; LORD JESUS CHRIST; and LORD HOLY SPIRIT!! instead of dwellingon "Angels" and leaving "GOD" out of the picture!! The greatest purpose of life is living it to the fullest within GOD's WAY!!!!!  NotANGELS!!! (WHOM ARE MERELY MESSSENGERS)!!!! AND WE AS HUMAN BEINGS HAVE SOMETHING EVEN BETTER THAN ANGELS - IT'S CALLED THE BIBLE!!!!  BASIS, INSTRUCTIONS, BEFORE, LEAVING EARTH!!!!  THANK YOU!!  MRS. D.L. WC.SEPT. 17, 2013

reviewText: I wish to thank Paramount for bringing this  wonderful show back to us Christians, and others who believe in our heavenly father regardless of the name given him. You folks at Paramount must have been touched by an Angel. I specifically enjoyed the episode where Jesus, named Zack was convicted of murder in a small town, to protect a retarded man who accidently set a school fire, killing all the students.. Monica stops a few paces from him and gives a small bow. Forgive me, I didnt know who you were, she says. They hardly ever do, Monica, he answers. She asks why she wasnt able to recognize him. He answers her, because you would do anything for me, but look what you did for a stranger. And greater love hath no person, nor angel then to give her life for another. Well done good and faithful servant. Monica looks down, when she looks back up, Zack is gone, but the dove remains where it had been. Monica, crying hears the doves cry and looks down, as if seeing it for the first time. The dove takes wing and flies off.So moving i cried.
summary: Paramount was touched by an Angel.

reviewText: Thank you so much CBS/Paramount and Amazon for this extraordinary gift.  The "Angels" in this, The Eighth Season, will definitely keep me warm through our southern winter.  Some standout episodes here include: Famous Last Words; Angels' Anonymous; A Winter Carol, and The Impossible Dream (featuring a truly soulful performance by Luther Vandross).  This episode is a biographical account of the man whose incredible contribution to the Soul Music Industry will live on forever.  Long live Luther Vandross.
summary: The Angels will keep me warm through our southern winter.

reviewText: I ordered and watched all seasons of Touched by an Angel. In our home, we work hard to keep the more pleasant things accented and the cares of the world at a minimum. TBAA  is TV watching that uses the different cares of the world and shows a positive way to get through and out the other side. Not all the good guys win or live and not all the bad guys lose and die. This being the case, the BIGGER picture is the focus and the outcome is positive.

reviewText: With nearly half of the ENTIRE SERIES already available on DVD, you'd think the next logical step would be to release Season 5, right? CBS and Paramount has apparently dropped this idea, and will only be releasing "collections" of the episodes that are considered the "best". There are only 4 episodes on each set, some have been released on DVD already.I know I should be happy but I'm not. I assume this is for financial reasons (not like CBS and Paramount combined are hurting) and this is better than nothing but it is a lame attempt to appease the fans when nearly half of the series on DVD has been released already. Nearly every tv show known to man is being released on DVD, and they pull a stunt like this? I would say this release should not be supported, but I fear if it's not they will never release seasons of TBAA on DVD again. This is truly a disappointment, and that's an understatement.
Title: Touched by an Angel: Season 8
